reviews.text:
Great pie and quick service.
Was doubtful when we pulled in. Only two cars
Went in and were seated right away.
Saw only one other couple.
Asked the server for the best on the menu and got a pleasant surprise.
Definitely coming back and trying the pasta üòç
Great place with great food. Service a tad slow but that's because it was prime time and really busy because it's really good. Overall, very pleased.

The food was great and the staff was friendly and helpful. They offer a military discount. The pizzas we got were fresh and hot when they came out. We had the BBQ brisket, yummy. The meat lovers delicious, and a pepperoni and a cheese pizza for the kids. Definitely be coming back here again to try new items.

I grew up with Pagliai's in MN. Absolutely love it.  The reason I did not rate a 5 is there was minimal sauce. Dry.  Honestly, their sauce is why they stand out. Need to increase sauce amount. That said, everyone needs to try pagliai's

Pagliai's (sounds like, Polly-Eyes) came highly recommended by coworkers as we are new to the area. My kids are Pizza and Pasta critics respectively and they were both pleased. Tough critics and they were impressed. Price is fair, close to $15-20 per person. I liked the Italian Stroganoff, my son enjoyed the pizza, and the others had alfredo. All were happy and a nice classic pizza place atmosphere with an open kitchen.

editorial_summary.overview: Comfy, bustling, family-run eatery featuring stone-oven pizzas plus pasta, subs, wine & beer.

detailedReviews.text: We have been dining here for Father‚Äôs Day for several years; it is my husband‚Äôs favorite. Unfortunately, our service tonight was terrible and I‚Äôm not sure we‚Äôll be back. Our meal took 2 hours & 20 min, and all we had was garlic bread and pizza. It was a full hour from when we got there and when our garlic bread order came. Our server apologized for the delay the first time she came to our table (to take our drink order about 15 minutes after we‚Äôd been seated), but at no point did she, or one of the hosts, or a manager come around to tables and explain the delay. I think it was because they had so many carry out orders, but that‚Äôs just a guess. Everyone in our section was waiting the same amount of time.
